I’m curious to see if Igus is the most common brand given the fact that they can be a bit pricey compared to other companies. We got ours off of Amazon because of how much cheaper it was. It worked great and was large enough to run 3 motors worth and 3 sensors worth of wiring. It did have some short comings. At our first comp it was very prone to popping but we solved this by our second competition.

We got ours from WestCoast Products and were very happy with it. We used the semi-enclosed 15x30mm version. The side of each link can snap off making it very easy to run the wire after the chain is installed as well as replace links if there is damage.

WestCoast Products

Cable Carriers

Energy chain is the industry standard for cable management, especially when it comes to moving systems. WCP carries both single direction and bi directional energy chain useful for both elevators and turrets. Access User Guide, Kit Contents &...

Price: USD 14.99

CTRE also stocks it.

Honestly? The bin in the corner labeled “e-chain.” It used to come in the KoP every year, whether or not you actually needed it.

Igus really had a knack for giving FRC teams a boatload of stuff they didn’t use. I swear every team that’s at least 15 years old has a crate full of these things, and none of them have EVER been used:

4LFK9_AS011072×1072 148 KB

To answer your question OP, if you’re in a pinch, go ask an old team in your area. There’s a chance they have a tote packed to the gills with more e-chain than they’ll ever use.
